cs.HCI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper introduces an interactive environment for visual layout composition via conversational interactions, which falls under the domain of HCI.
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The system involves conversational interactions between multiple agents, which can be analyzed from a natural language processing perspective.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The system involves placing objects in an editable canvas, which requires spatial and geometric reasoning, and can be analyzed from a computer vision perspective.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The system involves multiple agents with different roles and comprehensive quality controls, which can be analyzed from an AI perspective.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The system involves visual layout composition and can be used to build multimodal goal-oriented dialog tasks, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
